ion 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet. \r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study. \r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch. \r\n\r\nOptional\r\nStudents are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk</strong>\r\n7.1 Register for Waiver Tests\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Waiver Tests \r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:\r\n•  Academic Writing Exemption Test \r\n•  Optional Waiver Test for Statistics (Registration Deadline: 11 July) \r\n•  Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202 (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n7.2 Register for Camps \r\n\r\n7.2.1 Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (4 runs)\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Camps \r\n\r\n7.2.2 Please click here to register for other camps:\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n7.3 Register for Talks/Workshop\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Talks\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:\r\n•  Community Service Briefing \r\n•  Career Services Orientation\r\n•  Library T