login)\r\nNavigation Path: Self Service> Online Matriculation > Activate SMU Computer Account\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID & Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 5 - Upload Photograph</strong>\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). Approved photographs will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011, 5.00pm.\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 6 - Update Bank Information</strong>\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Update Bank Information \r\n\r\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\nMandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online AND \r\n- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet. \r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study. \r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch. \r\n\r\nOptional\r\nStudents are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk</strong>\r\n7.1 Register for Waiver Tests\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Waiver Tests \r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:\r\n•  Academic Writing Exemption Test \r\n•  Optional Waiver Test for Statistics (Registration Deadline: 11 July) \r\n•  Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202 (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n7.2 Register for Camps \r\n\r\n7.2.1 Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (4 runs)\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Camps \r\n\r\n7.2.2 Please click here to register for other camps:\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n7.3 Register for Talks/Workshop\r\nLogin to Student Portal OASIS (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\nNavigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Talks\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:\r\n•  Community Service Briefing \r\n•  Career Services Orientation\r\n•  Library Training Workshop \r\n\r\n<strong>Step 8 - Fee Matters & Financial Services</strong>\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\nFee Payment\r\nPayment Mode\r\nTuition Grant Application\r\nStudent Financial Assistance Schemes\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 9 - Other Important Information</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n•  Academic Calendar (PDF) \r\n•  Exemption Criteria \r\n•  Double Degree\r\n•  Leave of Absence\r\n•  Withdrawal\r\n•  SMU Student Card \r\n•  Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card\r\n•  Student Locker \r\n•  Student Insurance \r\n•  PC/Notebook Offer','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-10','','','2012-04-24 09:30:02','2012-04-24 09:30:02','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(107,1,'2012-04-24 10:11:50','2012-04-24 10:11:50','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\" width=1024 height=400 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment(at least 2 days prior to step 3)\"]Login to Applicant\'s Self Service (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\nNavigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of $203 via credit card** or AXS Payment Stations available island-wide.\r\nNote: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n*One-Time Fee of S$203 (non-refundable) for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation (NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission).\r\n**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via Applicant\'s Self Service.\r\nYou may check the payment 