u.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p> Please take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 3 Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n      <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong><br>\r\n        <br>        \r\n        <p>Please ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.</p>\r\n        <p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students <span class=\"red\">below 18 years old</span>, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n        <table width=\"500px\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"500\" bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" ><div class=\"ctrtext\"><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION<br>\r\n                <br> \r\n                Date: 18 June 2012, 9.00am - 16 July 2012, 5.00pm</strong>\r\n                \r\n                <br>\r\n                <br>\r\n                (Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by <span class=\"red\">12 July 2012</span>. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.) <br>\r\n                </div></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n [/accordion]\r\n\r\n        [accordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong> Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong> </p>\r\n<p>Please remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as\r\n\r\n\r\nthe student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.</p>\r\n        <p>Henceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly. </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      [/accordion]\r\n      \r\n[/accordions]      \r\n','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-37','','','2012-04-30 04:54:14','2012-04-30 04:54:14','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-37/',0,'revision','',0),(111,1,'2012-04-24 10:39:29','2012-04-24 10:39:29','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment(at least 2 days prior to step 3)\"]Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-16','','','2012-04-24 10:39:29','2012-04-24 10:39:29','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(110,1,'2012-04-24 10:16:04','2012-04-24 10:16:04','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment(at least 2 days prior to step 3)\"]Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment\r\n\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Second title\"]Second accordion content[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-15','','','2012-04-24 10:16:04','2012-04-24 10:16:04','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2012-04-30 04:51:37','2012-04-30 04:51:37','[accordions title=\"Accordion Group Title\" active=1 event=\"click\" autoheight=true]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 1 - Make Payment (at least 2 days prior to Step 3)\"]\r\n<div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment <br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        </strong>        \r\n        <p>Make non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by<span class=\"red\"> 12 July 2012</span>. </p>\r\n        <div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n            <p align=\"justify\"><b>*One-Time Fee of S$203</b> <b><strong>(non-refundable) </strong></b>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <font color=red>(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</font>. </p>\r\n            <p align=\"justify\" > \r\n      **The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" >You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    [/accordion]\r\n    [accordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n	         <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p> Please take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 3 - <span class=\"red\">Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n      <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong><br>\r\n        <br>        \r\n        <p>Please ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.</p>\r\n        <p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students <span class=\"red\">below 18 years old</span>, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n        <table width=\"500px\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"500\" bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" ><div class=\"ctrtext\"><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION<br>\r\n                <br> \r\n                Date: 18 June 2012, 9.00am - 16 July 2012, 5.00pm</strong>\r\n                \r\n                <br>\r\n                <br>\r\n                (Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by <span class=\"red\">12 July 2012</span>. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.) <br>\r\n                </div></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n [/accordion]\r\n\r\n        [accordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong> Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong> </p>\r\n<p>Please remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as\r\n\r\n\r\nthe student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.</p>\r\n        <p>Henceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly. </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      [/accordion]\r\n      \r\n[/accordions]    ','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-35','','','2012-04-30 04:51:37','2012-04-30 04:51:37','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-35/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2012-04-26 11:58:08','2012-04-26 11:58:08','   <div id=\"accordion\">  \r\n       <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 1 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk</a></h3>\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p><strong>1.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests<br>\r\n          </strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests <br>\r\n          <br>\r\n          </strong>Please click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong><br>\r\n          </strong> &#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July) <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 23 July)</p>\r\n        <p><strong>1.2 </strong><strong> Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps <br>\r\n          <br>\r\n          </strong><strong>1.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)<br>\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong> <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>1.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:<br>\r\n</strong>&#149;&nbsp; SSU Sports Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMUX Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SICS Freshmen Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMU Arts Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; School Camps</p>\r\n        <p><strong>1.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop<br>\r\n          </strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks<br>\r\n          <br>\r\n          </strong>Please click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong><br>\r\n          </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/Freshmen%202012_C4SR.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a></p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 2 - \r\n\r\n\r\n Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services</a> </h3>\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p><br>\r\n          Please click on the following links for information: </p>\r\n        <ul><li><strong><a href=\"fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment </a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n          <li><strong><a href=\"financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong> </li>\r\n          <li><strong><a href=\"financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a> </strong></li>\r\n          <li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong> </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n       </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 3 - Other Important Information</a> </h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p><br>\r\n    Please click on the following links for information:<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <strong><a href=\"downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202012-13.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF) <br>\r\n    </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree<br>\r\n</strong></a><strong>&#149;&nbsp; </strong><a href=\"Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence<br>\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong><strong>&#149;&nbsp; </strong></strong><a href=\"Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong><br>\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong>&#149;&nbsp; </strong><a href=\"service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card<br>\r\n    </strong></a>&#149;&nbsp; <strong><a href=\"service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a><br>\r\n    </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer </strong></a></p>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 4 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period </a> </h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p><br>\r\n    Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk </strong></p>\r\n            <p><strong>List of Tests </strong><strong><br>\r\n              </strong><strong> </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a></p>\r\n            <p><strong>List of Camps<br>\r\n              </strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong><br>\r\n              </strong>&#149;&nbsp; SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SSU Sports Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMUX Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SICS Freshmen Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL) </p>\r\n            <p><strong>List of Talks/Workshop<br>\r\n              </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/Freshmen%202012_C4SR.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a> <br>\r\n            </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 5 - <span class=\"red\">IDs Verification Period </span></a></h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <div class=\"ctrtext\">    \r\n              <p>Previously matriculated NSMen are still  required  to come back during the<a href=\"verification_NS.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> IDs Verification period (30 July to 1 August 2012)</strong></a> for the purpose of submitting financial forms, attending the Library Training session and the Notebook Fair.\r\n                </p>\r\n              <div class=\"ctrtext\">\r\n      <table width=\"0%\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n        <tr>\r\n          <td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\" class=\"ctrtext\"><p align=\"center\"><span class=\"style4\">Venue</span><br>\r\n            <strong>School of Accountancy <br>\r\n  Registration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong> <br>\r\n  Singapore Management University <br>\r\n  60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900 </p>\r\n            <p align=\"center\"><span class=\"style4\">Date &amp; Time </span><strong><br>\r\n                </strong><strong><strong>30 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm <br>\r\n                </strong> </strong>(<strong><span class=\"style2\">Note: </span></strong>1st day session starts at 2.00pm<strong>) <br>\r\n                <strong>31 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm <br>\r\n1 August: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong> </p></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n      </table>\r\n      <p align=\"center\"><br>\r\n        Please <a href=\"verification_NS.asp\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"bodytext red red\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong><span class=\"red\">COMPULSORY</span> documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 6 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period </a> </h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p><strong>6.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)</p>\r\n            <p><strong>6.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk </strong><strong></strong></p>\r\n            <p><strong>List of Tests </strong><strong><br>\r\n            </strong><strong> </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a></p>\r\n            <p><strong>List of Camps<br>\r\n              </strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong><br>\r\n              </strong>&#149;&nbsp; SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMU Arts Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS) </p>\r\n            <p><strong>List of Talks/Workshop<br>\r\n              </strong> &#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a></p>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 7 - Register for Classes </a></h3>\r\n          <div> \r\n            <p>At SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes. </p>\r\n            <p>Please <a href=\"aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS. </p> \r\n            </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">Step 8 - Attend Convocation</a></h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p>Convocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU. </p>\r\n            <p>Please <a href=\"www.smu.edu.sg/convocation\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation. </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n<h3><a href=\"#\">Start of Term</a> </h3>\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p><strong>OASIS </strong></p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note: </strong></span>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>! <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n            <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent <strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>. <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n  Please click <a href=\"downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS. </p>\r\n        <p>You are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life. <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n  If you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact: <br>\r\n  <strong><br>\r\n  IITS HelpDesk </strong><br>\r\n  Singapore Management University <br>\r\n  Basement 1, School of Accountancy <br>\r\n  Singapore 188065 <br>\r\n  Tel: +65 6828 0123 <br>\r\n  Email: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a><br>\r\n  <br>\r\n  <em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em><br>\r\n  Mon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm) </p>\r\n        <span class=\"red\"><strong>Reminder... </strong></span><br>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a> on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        \r\n\r\n<!-- insert content for 3rd column  here -->\r\n		</div>\r\n</div>\r\n','Matriculated NSMen','','inherit','open','open','','157-revision-4','','','2012-04-26 11:58:08','2012-04-26 11:58:08','',157,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/157-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(156,1,'2012-04-25 10:24:14','2012-04-25 10:24:14','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\n\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in <strong><em>August 2011</em></strong>. You must complete the registration formalities (both <strong>Part 1 </strong>and <strong>Part 2</strong>) according to the schedule below.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE:\r\n</strong>\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 1 - Apply for Student Pass\"]\r\nIn accordance with the Immigration Act, any foreigner who is not a Singapore Permanent Resident, and wishes to study at SMU, is required to apply for a Student\'s Pass.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nSMU will be acting as your sponsor for the application and will advise you on the Student\'s Pass application procedures.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/predeparture.asp#studentpass\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on student\'s pass application. Kindly email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg</a> for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step2 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: International Students may proceed to matriculate online only after you have been notified of your Student\'s Pass Approval via email. Please email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg </a>for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div><strong><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong></strong>Date: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm(session closed)For those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong>\r\n\r\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>8.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>8.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n8.4</strong><strong> Register for International Students\' Orientation Programmes </strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree</strong></a><strong>\r\n•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong><strong>•  </strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong> <strong>\r\n</strong></a>•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>International Student Affairs</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>18 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up. Kindly print and bring <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/ICA_SMU%20Medical%20Report%20(Revised).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>this form (ICA format)</strong></a> to the RMG clinic.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong><strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong>(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>14.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a></strong> (This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>14.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please<strong> <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></strong> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 16 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-7','','','2012-04-25 10:24:14','2012-04-25 10:24:14','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(112,1,'2012-04-24 12:42:59','2012-04-24 12:42:59','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-17','','','2012-04-24 12:42:59','2012-04-24 12:42:59','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(114,1,'2012-04-24 12:50:41','2012-04-24 12:50:41','','blu_stripes','','inherit','open','open','','blu_stripes','','','2012-04-24 12:50:41','2012-04-24 12:50:41','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/blu_stripes.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(113,1,'2012-04-24 12:46:19','2012-04-24 12:46:19','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion valign=\"bottom\" title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-18','','','2012-04-24 12:46:19','2012-04-24 12:46:19','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(115,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:38','2012-04-25 01:54:38','','matric_banner01_furmston','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner01_furmston','','','2012-04-25 01:54:38','2012-04-25 01:54:38','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner01_furmston.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(116,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:41','2012-04-25 01:54:41','','matric_banner02_raj','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner02_raj','','','2012-04-25 01:54:41','2012-04-25 01:54:41','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner02_raj.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(117,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:44','2012-04-25 01:54:44','','matric_banner03_stevemiller','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner03_stevemiller','','','2012-04-25 01:54:44','2012-04-25 01:54:44','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner03_stevemiller.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(118,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:47','2012-04-25 01:54:47','','matric_banner04_yanghoong','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner04_yanghoong','','','2012-04-25 01:54:47','2012-04-25 01:54:47','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner04_yanghoong.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(119,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:50','2012-04-25 01:54:50','','matric_banner05_howardthomas','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner05_howardthomas','','','2012-04-25 01:54:50','2012-04-25 01:54:50','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner05_howardthomas.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(120,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:53','2012-04-25 01:54:53','','matric_banner06_jamestang','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner06_jamestang','','','2012-04-25 01:54:53','2012-04-25 01:54:53','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner06_jamestang.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(121,1,'2012-04-25 01:54:55','2012-04-25 01:54:55','','matric_banner07_phangsockyong','','inherit','open','open','','matric_banner07_phangsockyong','','','2012-04-25 01:54:55','2012-04-25 01:54:55','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matric_banner07_phangsockyong.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(122,1,'2012-04-24 12:46:39','2012-04-24 12:46:39','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-19','','','2012-04-24 12:46:39','2012-04-24 12:46:39','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(123,1,'2012-04-23 02:43:50','2012-04-23 02:43:50','This is a home page','Index','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-6','','','2012-04-23 02:43:50','2012-04-23 02:43:50','',2,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/2-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(124,1,'2012-04-23 08:49:07','2012-04-23 08:49:07','','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-2','','','2012-04-23 08:49:07','2012-04-23 08:49:07','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(130,1,'2012-04-26 11:48:02','2012-04-26 11:48:02','','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-autosave','','','2012-04-26 11:48:02','2012-04-26 11:48:02','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(125,1,'2012-04-23 08:49:48','2012-04-23 08:49:48','','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-2','','','2012-04-23 08:49:48','2012-04-23 08:49:48','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(148,1,'2012-04-25 03:30:43','2012-04-25 03:30:43','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-20','','','2012-04-25 03:30:43','2012-04-25 03:30:43','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(127,1,'2012-04-25 09:30:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-04-25 09:30:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/?page_id=127',0,'page','',0),(126,1,'2012-04-25 10:25:21','2012-04-25 10:25:21','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\n\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in <strong><em>August 2011</em></strong>. You must complete the registration formalities (both <strong>Part 1 </strong>and <strong>Part 2</strong>) according to the schedule below.\n\n<strong>NOTE:\n</strong>\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\n\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\n\n[haccordion title=\"Step 1 - Apply for Student Pass\"]\nIn accordance with the Immigration Act, any foreigner who is not a Singapore Permanent Resident, and wishes to study at SMU, is required to apply for a Student\'s Pass.\n<div>\n\nSMU will be acting as your sponsor for the application and will advise you on the Student\'s Pass application procedures.\n\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/predeparture.asp#studentpass\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on student\'s pass application. Kindly email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg</a> for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\n\n</div>\n[/haccordion]\n\n[haccordion title=\"Step2 Make Payment\"]\n\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n<div>\n\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\n\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n[/haccordion]\n\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\n\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\n\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\n\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\n\n<strong>Note</strong>: International Students may proceed to matriculate online only after you have been notified of your Student\'s Pass Approval via email. Please email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg </a>for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\n\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\n\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\n\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\n<div><strong><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong></strong>Date: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm(session closed)For those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)</div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\n\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\n\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\n\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\n\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Upload Photograph\"]\n\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\n\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\n\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\n\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Update Bank Information\"]\n<div>\n\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong>\n\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\n\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\n\nAll students are required to :\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\n\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\n\n<strong>Optional\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\n\n</div>\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\n\n<strong>8.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\n\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\n\n<strong>8.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\n\n<strong>8.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\n\n<strong>8.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\n•  SMUX Camp\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\n•  SMU Arts Camp\n•  School Camps\n\n<strong>8.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\n\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\n\n<strong>\n8.4</strong><strong> Register for International Students\' Orientation Programmes </strong>\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\n\n<strong>\n</strong>\n<div></div>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\n<ul>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Other Important Information\"]\nPlease click on the following links for information:\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree</strong></a><strong>\n•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence\n</strong></strong></a><strong><strong>•  </strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\n</strong></strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong> <strong>\n</strong></a>•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\n•  <strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>International Student Affairs</strong></a>\n<div></div>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\n\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\n\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>18 July 2011</strong>.\n\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up. Kindly print and bring <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/ICA_SMU%20Medical%20Report%20(Revised).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>this form (ICA format)</strong></a> to the RMG clinic.\n\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\n<div>\n\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\n\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\n\n<strong>List of Camps\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\n•  SSU Sports Camp\n•  SMUX Camp\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\n\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\n\n</div>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\n</strong>\n<strong>School of Accountancy\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\nSingapore Management University\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n<div>\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\n<strong><strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong>(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).</p>\n\n</div>\n<strong>\n</strong>\n\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\n<div>\n\n<strong>14.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a></strong> (This is crucial)\n\n<strong>14.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\n\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\n</strong><strong></strong>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\n\n<strong>List of Camps\n</strong>Please<strong> <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></strong> for information on the camps:<strong>\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\n•  SMU Arts Camp\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\n\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\n\n<strong>\n</strong>\n\n</div>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Register for Classes\"]\n\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\n\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\n\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Step 16 - Attend Convocation\"]\n<div>\n\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\n\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\n\n</div>\n[/haccordion]\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\n<div>\n\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\n\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\n\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\n\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\n\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\n\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\n<strong>\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\nSingapore Management University\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\nSingapore 188065\nTel: +65 6828 0123\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\n\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\n\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\n</strong>\n\n</div>\n[/haccordion]\n[/haccordions]\n<strong>\n</strong>','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-autosave','','','2012-04-25 10:25:21','2012-04-25 10:25:21','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(128,1,'2012-04-25 09:37:11','2012-04-25 09:37:11','','bg','','inherit','open','open','','bg','','','2012-04-25 09:37:11','2012-04-25 09:37:11','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/bg.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(129,1,'2012-04-25 09:17:40','2012-04-25 09:17:40','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-3','','','2012-04-25 09:17:40','2012-04-25 09:17:40','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(155,1,'2012-04-25 10:21:01','2012-04-25 10:21:01','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\n\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in <strong><em>August 2011</em></strong>. You must complete the registration formalities (both <strong>Part 1 </strong>and <strong>Part 2</strong>) according to the schedule below.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>NOTE:\r\n</strong>\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2011.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.</p>\r\n[haccordions title=\"A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment(at least 2 days prior to step 3)\"]Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation (NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission).</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\"><strong><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong></strong>Date: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm(session closed)For those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011, 5.00pm.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong>\r\n\r\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong><strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011 , 5.00pm)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.\r\n\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-6','','','2012-04-25 10:21:01','2012-04-25 10:21:01','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2012-04-25 09:49:19','2012-04-25 09:49:19','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment(at least 2 days prior to step 3)\"]Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment\r\n\r\n</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation (NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission).</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\"><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm </strong>(session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011, 5.00pm.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information\r\n\r\n</strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests\r\n\r\n</strong>Please click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks\r\n\r\n</strong>Please click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n\r\n</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n</strong>(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n\r\n</strong>(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011 , 5.00pm)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.\r\n\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-4','','','2012-04-25 09:49:19','2012-04-25 09:49:19','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(132,1,'2012-04-25 09:18:20','2012-04-25 09:18:20','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-3','','','2012-04-25 09:18:20','2012-04-25 09:18:20','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(133,1,'2012-04-25 10:14:31','2012-04-25 10:14:31','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\n\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in <strong><em>August 2011</em></strong>. You must complete the registration formalities (both <strong>Part 1 </strong>and <strong>Part 2</strong>) according to the schedule below.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE:\r\n</strong>\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 1 - Apply for Student Pass\"]\r\nIn accordance with the Immigration Act, any foreigner who is not a Singapore Permanent Resident, and wishes to study at SMU, is required to apply for a Student\'s Pass.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nSMU will be acting as your sponsor for the application and will advise you on the Student\'s Pass application procedures.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/predeparture.asp#studentpass\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on student\'s pass application. Kindly email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg</a> for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step2 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment\r\n\r\n</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: International Students may proceed to matriculate online only after you have been notified of your Student\'s Pass Approval via email. Please email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg </a>for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm </strong>(session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information\r\n\r\n</strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>8.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests\r\n\r\n</strong>Please click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps\r\n\r\n</strong><strong>8.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>8.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks\r\n\r\n</strong>Please click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n8.4</strong><strong> Register for International Students\' Orientation Programmes </strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree</strong></a><strong>\r\n•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong><strong>•  </strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong> <strong>\r\n</strong></a>•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>International Student Affairs</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>18 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up. Kindly print and bring <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/ICA_SMU%20Medical%20Report%20(Revised).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>this form (ICA format)</strong></a> to the RMG clinic.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n\r\n</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong>\r\n\r\n25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n</strong>(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n\r\n</strong>(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>14.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a></strong> (This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>14.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please<strong> <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></strong> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 16 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-4','','','2012-04-25 10:14:31','2012-04-25 10:14:31','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(134,1,'2012-04-25 10:14:44','2012-04-25 10:14:44','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\n\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in <strong><em>August 2011</em></strong>. You must complete the registration formalities (both <strong>Part 1 </strong>and <strong>Part 2</strong>) according to the schedule below.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE:\r\n</strong>\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 1 - Apply for Student Pass\"]\r\nIn accordance with the Immigration Act, any foreigner who is not a Singapore Permanent Resident, and wishes to study at SMU, is required to apply for a Student\'s Pass.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nSMU will be acting as your sponsor for the application and will advise you on the Student\'s Pass application procedures.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/predeparture.asp#studentpass\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on student\'s pass application. Kindly email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg</a> for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step2 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: International Students may proceed to matriculate online only after you have been notified of your Student\'s Pass Approval via email. Please email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg </a>for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div><strong><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong></strong>Date: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm\r\n\r\n(session closed)For those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong>\r\n\r\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>8.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>8.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n8.4</strong><strong> Register for International Students\' Orientation Programmes </strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree</strong></a><strong>\r\n•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong><strong>•  </strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong> <strong>\r\n</strong></a>•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>International Student Affairs</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>18 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up. Kindly print and bring <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/ICA_SMU%20Medical%20Report%20(Revised).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>this form (ICA format)</strong></a> to the RMG clinic.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong><strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>14.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a></strong> (This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>14.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please<strong> <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></strong> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 16 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-5','','','2012-04-25 10:14:44','2012-04-25 10:14:44','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(135,1,'2012-04-25 09:51:57','2012-04-25 09:51:57','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment(at least 2 days prior to step 3)\"]Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation (NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission).</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\"><strong><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong></strong>Date: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm\r\n\r\n(session closed)For those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011, 5.00pm.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong>\r\n\r\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong><strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by 15 July 2011 , 5.00pm)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.\r\n\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-5','','','2012-04-25 09:51:57','2012-04-25 09:51:57','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(136,1,'2012-04-25 10:19:27','2012-04-25 10:19:27','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\n\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in <strong><em>August 2011</em></strong>. You must complete the registration formalities (both <strong>Part 1 </strong>and <strong>Part 2</strong>) according to the schedule below.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE:\r\n</strong>\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 1 - Apply for Student Pass\"]\r\nIn accordance with the Immigration Act, any foreigner who is not a Singapore Permanent Resident, and wishes to study at SMU, is required to apply for a Student\'s Pass.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nSMU will be acting as your sponsor for the application and will advise you on the Student\'s Pass application procedures.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/predeparture.asp#studentpass\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on student\'s pass application. Kindly email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg</a> for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step2 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2011.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 3 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: International Students may proceed to matriculate online only after you have been notified of your Student\'s Pass Approval via email. Please email<a href=\"mailto:admissions@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">admissions@smu.edu.sg </a>for enquiries on student\'s pass matters.\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div><strong><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong></strong>Date: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm(session closed)For those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 7 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong>\r\n\r\nUpdate your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>\r\n\r\nAll students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.\r\n\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.\r\n\r\n<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 8 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>8.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>8.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>8.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n8.4</strong><strong> Register for International Students\' Orientation Programmes </strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 9 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]Please click on the following links for information:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SPR&amp;IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 10 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree</strong></a><strong>\r\n•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong><strong>•  </strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong> <strong>\r\n</strong></a>•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong></strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>International Student Affairs</strong></a>\r\n<div></div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 11 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\n\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>18 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up. Kindly print and bring <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/ICA_SMU%20Medical%20Report%20(Revised).pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>this form (ICA format)</strong></a> to the RMG clinic.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 12 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 13 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE\r\n</strong>\r\n<strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong><strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_FS.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>14.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a></strong> (This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>14.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please<strong> <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></strong> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Orientation Programmes\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/international_students/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">International Student Affairs</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 15 - Register for Classes\"]\r\n\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 16 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[/haccordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','International Student','','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-6','','','2012-04-25 10:19:27','2012-04-25 10:19:27','',88,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/88-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(137,1,'2012-04-26 01:33:58','2012-04-26 01:33:58','','lghtmesh','','inherit','open','open','','lghtmesh','','','2012-04-26 01:33:58','2012-04-26 01:33:58','',0,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/lghtmesh.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(138,1,'2012-04-26 03:02:22','2012-04-26 03:02:22','','logo','','inherit','open','open','','logo-2','','','2012-04-26 03:02:22','2012-04-26 03:02:22','',0,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(141,1,'2012-04-26 04:01:08','2012-04-26 04:01:08','','spore_PR','','inherit','open','open','','spore_pr','','','2012-04-26 04:01:08','2012-04-26 04:01:08','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/spore_PR.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(142,1,'2012-04-26 04:01:21','2012-04-26 04:01:21','','international-students','','inherit','open','open','','international-students','','','2012-04-26 04:01:21','2012-04-26 04:01:21','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/international-students.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(143,1,'2012-04-26 04:06:26','2012-04-26 04:06:26','','smu_logo_260x60','','inherit','open','open','','smu_logo_260x60','','','2012-04-26 04:06:26','2012-04-26 04:06:26','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/smu_logo_260x60.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(145,1,'2012-04-26 04:21:34','2012-04-26 04:21:34','','2matric-468x60','','inherit','open','open','','2matric-468x60','','','2012-04-26 04:21:34','2012-04-26 04:21:34','',4,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/2matric-468x60.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(146,1,'2012-04-26 09:08:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-04-26 09:08:34','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/?p=146',0,'post','',0),(147,1,'2012-04-26 09:31:40','2012-04-26 09:31:40','','matriculated-nsmen','','inherit','open','open','','matriculated-nsmen','','','2012-04-26 09:31:40','2012-04-26 09:31:40','',0,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/matriculated-nsmen.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(149,1,'2012-04-26 11:33:31','2012-04-26 11:33:31','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[haccordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>\r\n\r\n(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[/accordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-21','','','2012-04-26 11:33:31','2012-04-26 11:33:31','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(150,1,'2012-04-26 11:34:27','2012-04-26 11:34:27','A warm welcome to Singapore Management University!\r\nAll successful applicants who have accepted SMU\'s offer are required to register as students of the University before commencing their studies in August 2012. You must complete the registration formalities (both Part 1 and Part 2) according to the schedule below.\r\nNOTE:\r\n\r\n- This matriculation exercise is only applicable to students who are commencing their studies in August 2012.\r\n\r\n- Applicants who have just accepted the offer would need to allow 3 working days before proceeding to perform online matriculation.\r\n[accordions title=\"\" width=950 height=450 hwidth=28 speed=200 active=1]\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step1 Make Payment\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMake non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2012/downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by 30 July 2012.\r\n<div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong>*One-Time Fee of S$203</strong> <strong>(non-refundable) </strong>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <span style=\"color: red;\">(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</span>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">**The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via<a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong>\r\n\r\nPlease take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 3 - Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students below 18 years old, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"500px\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" width=\"500\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 13 June 2011, 9.00am - 11 July 2011, 5.00pm (session closed)\r\n\r\nFor those who missed the session, Office of the Registrar will be sending the <em><strong>2nd round of Online Matriculation / IDs Verification exercise</strong></em> details via email.\r\n\r\n(Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by 30 July 2011. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)\r\n\r\n</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.\r\n\r\nHenceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Upload Student Photograph</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease use the newly activated account and login to the student portal<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg). <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected.\r\n\r\nNote: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011, 5.00pm</span>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n<div>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information</strong></strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study.<strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details*</strong>All students are required to :\r\n- update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via \"Finance Office\" drop box by end August 2011, if the bank account has not been opened yet.Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study.\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch.<strong>Optional\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nLogin to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July)\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 25 July)\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2 </strong><strong>Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:\r\n</strong>•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps\r\n\r\n<strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 8 - Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/fee_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a></strong><strong></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/financial_tga_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 9 - Other Important Information\"]\r\nPlease click on the following links for information:\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202011-12.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF)\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Leave of Absence\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  <strong></strong></strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong>\r\n</strong></a><strong>•  </strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a>\r\n•  <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a>\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up\"]\r\nAll students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <strong>COMPULSORY</strong>medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <strong>20 July 2011</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAttend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)\r\n•  SSU Sports Camp\r\n•  SMUX Camp\r\n•  SICS Freshmen Camp\r\n•  School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Briefing.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 12 - Part 2: IDs Verification\"]\r\n<strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>School of Accountancy\r\nRegistration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\n60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900\r\n<div>\r\n<table width=\"0%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\">Date &amp; Time <strong></strong>25 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n(Note: 1st day session starts at 2.00pm)\r\n<strong>26 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm\r\n27 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong>(Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">15 July 2011 , 5.00pm</span>)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p align=\"center\">Please <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/verification_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong>COMPULSORY documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n<strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial)\r\n\r\n<strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Tests </strong><strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Camps\r\n</strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong>\r\n</strong>•  SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)\r\n•  SMU Arts Camp\r\n•  School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS)\r\n\r\n<strong>List of Talks/Workshop\r\n</strong>•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a>\r\n•  <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/haccordion]\r\n[haccordion title=\"Step 14 - Register for Classes\"]\r\nAt SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 15 - Attend Convocation\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nConvocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU.\r\n\r\nPlease <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Start of Term\"]\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>OASIS</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a>(https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent<strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>.\r\n\r\nPlease click <a href=\"http://smu.edu.sg/matriculation/2011/downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS.\r\n\r\nYou are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life.\r\n\r\nIf you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact:\r\n<strong>\r\nIITS HelpDesk </strong>\r\nSingapore Management University\r\nBasement 1, School of Accountancy\r\nSingapore 188065\r\nTel: +65 6828 0123\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em>\r\nMon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm)\r\n\r\n<strong>Reminder... </strong>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg/\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a>on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[/accordions]\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>','Singaporean','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-22','','','2012-04-26 11:34:27','2012-04-26 11:34:27','',84,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/84-revision-22/',0,'revision','',0),(213,1,'2012-04-30 06:37:20','2012-04-30 06:37:20','[accordions title=\"Accordion Group Title\" active=1 event=\"click\" autoheight=true]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 1 - Make Payment (at least 2 days prior to Step 3)\"]\r\n<div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment <br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        </strong>        \r\n        <p>Make non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by<span class=\"red\"> 12 July 2012</span>. </p>\r\n        <div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n            <p align=\"justify\"><b>*One-Time Fee of S$203</b> <b><strong>(non-refundable) </strong></b>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <font color=red>(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</font>. </p>\r\n            <p align=\"justify\" > \r\n      **The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" >You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    [/accordion]\r\n    [accordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n	         <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p> Please take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 3 Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n      <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong><br>\r\n        <br>        \r\n        <p>Please ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.</p>\r\n        <p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students <span class=\"red\">below 18 years old</span>, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n        <table width=\"500px\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"500\" bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" ><div class=\"ctrtext\"><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION<br>\r\n                <br> \r\n                Date: 18 June 2012, 9.00am - 16 July 2012, 5.00pm</strong>\r\n                \r\n                <br>\r\n                <br>\r\n                (Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by <span class=\"red\">12 July 2012</span>. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.) <br>\r\n                </div></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n [/accordion]\r\n [accordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong> Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong> </p>\r\n<p>Please remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as\r\n\r\n\r\nthe student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.</p>\r\n        <p>Henceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly. </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      [/accordion]\r\n\r\n    \r\n       	\r\n	        [accordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n	\r\n	      <div>\r\n	       <p>Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph</strong></p>\r\n        <p>Please use the newly activated account and login to the student portal  <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg).\r\n      \r\n          <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">          Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"ctrtext\"><span class=\"style2\">Note:</span> Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012, 5.00pm</u>.</span></p>\r\n \r\n	      </div>\r\n	      [/accordion]\r\n    \r\n\r\n       \r\n [accordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information\"]\r\n	\r\n	      <div>\r\n	       <p>Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph</strong></p>\r\n        <p>Please use the newly activated account and login to the student portal  <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg).\r\n      \r\n          <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">          Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"ctrtext\"><span class=\"style2\">Note:</span> Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012, 5.00pm</u>.</span></p>\r\n \r\n	      </div>\r\n	      [/accordion]\r\n [accordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n	\r\n	      <div>\r\n	       <p>Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph</strong></p>\r\n        <p>Please use the newly activated account and login to the student portal  <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasi