nt Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"ctrtext\"><span class=\"style2\">Note:</span> Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012, 5.00pm</u>.</span></p>\r\n      </div>\r\n        <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 6 - Update Bank Information</a> </h3>\r\n        <div>\r\n          <p>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n            <strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n          </strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study. </p>\r\n          <p class=\"red\"><strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details* </strong></p>\r\n          <p>All students are required to :<br>\r\n            - update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND <br>\r\n            </strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via &quot;Finance Office&quot; drop box by end August 2012, if the bank account has not been opened yet. <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n            Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.<br>\r\n            * This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study. <br>\r\n            ** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch. <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n            <strong>Optional<br>\r\n            </strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n          </p></DIV>\r\n          \r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk</a></h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p><strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests<br>\r\n            </strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n              <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests <br>\r\n              <br>\r\n              </strong>Please click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong><br>\r\n              </strong>              &#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July) <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 23 July)</p>\r\n            <p><strong>7.2 </strong><strong> Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps <br>\r\n              <br>\r\n            </strong><strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)<br>\r\nLogin to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps </strong> <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click he