    </div>\r\n [/accordion]\r\n [accordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong> Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong> </p>\r\n<p>Please remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as\r\n\r\n\r\nthe student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.</p>\r\n        <p>Henceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly. </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      [/accordion]\r\n\r\n    \r\n       	\r\n	        [accordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n	\r\n	      <div>\r\n	       <p>Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph</strong></p>\r\n        <p>Please use the newly activated account and login to the student portal  <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg).\r\n      \r\n          <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">          Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"ctrtext\"><span class=\"style2\">Note:</span> Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012, 5.00pm</u>.</span></p>\r\n \r\n	      </div>\r\n	      [/accordion]\r\n    \r\n[accordion title=\"Step 6 - Update Bank Information</a> </h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n            <strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information <br>\r\n<br>\r\n</strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study. </p>\r\n<p class=\"red\"><strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details* </strong></p>\r\n<p>All students are required to :<br>\r\n            - update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND <br>\r\n</strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via &quot;Finance Office&quot; drop box by end August 2012, if the bank account has not been opened yet. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nStudents who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.<br>\r\n* This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study. <br>\r\n** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch. <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>Optional<br>\r\n</strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n</p></DIV>\r\n\r\n [/accordian]\r\n\r\n\r\n [accordion title=\"Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk\"]\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests<br>\r\n</strong>Login to <strong></st