 credit card** or <a href=\"downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide. </p>\r\n          <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by<span class=\"red\"> 12 July 2012</span>. </p>\r\n          <div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n              <p align=\"justify\"><b>*One-Time Fee of S$203</b> <b><strong>(non-refundable) </strong></b>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <font color=red>(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</font>. </p>\r\n              <p align=\"justify\" > **The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n              <p align=\"justify\" >You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).\r\n              </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data</a></h3>\r\n\r\n      <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong><br>\r\n        <br>        \r\n        <p> Please take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies. </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 3 - <span class=\"red\">Part 1: Matriculate Online</span> </a></h3>\r\n\r\n      <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong><br>\r\n        <br>        \r\n        <p>Please ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.</p>\r\n        <p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students <span class=\"red\">below 18 years old</span>, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n        <table width=\"500px\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"500\" bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" ><div class=\"ctrtext\"><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION<br>\r\n                <br> \r\n                Date: </strong><strong><strong>18 June 2012, 9.00am - 16 July 2012, 5.00pm</strong></strong>\r\n                <br>\r\n                <br>\r\n                (Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by <span class=\"red\">12 July 2011</span>. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.)                \r\n                </div></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account </a></h3>\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n          <strong> Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong> </p>\r\n        <p>Please remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as \r\n\r\n\r\n the student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.</p>\r\n        <p>Henceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly.</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 5 - Upload Photograph</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph</strong></p>\r\n        <p>Please use the newly activated account and login to the student portal  <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg).\r\n      \r\n          <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">          Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"ctrtext\"><span class=\"style2\">Note:</span> Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012, 5.00pm</u>. </span></p>\r\n      </div>\r\n        <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 6 - Update Bank Information</a> </h3>\r\n        <div>\r\n          <p>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n            <strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Update Bank Information <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n          </strong>Update your bank information for reimbursement of claims that you may have during your course of study. </p>\r\n          <p class=\"red\"><strong>Mandatory Field to Update - Bank Account Details* </strong></p>\r\n          <p>All students are required to :<br>\r\n            - update their Singapore-based bank account** details online <strong>AND <br>\r\n            </strong>- submit a hardcopy of their bank details to the Office of Finance (Station 2) during the ID Verification Day, or via &quot;Finance Office&quot; drop box by end August 2012, if the bank account has not been opened yet. <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n            Students who do not have any Singapore-based bank account are required to open the account to meet the above mandatory requirement.<br>\r\n            * This is to facilitate funds (eg. scholarship/reimbursements) to be credited into your account during the entire course of study. <br>\r\n            ** This refer to bank accounts maintained with the Singapore branch. <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n            <strong>Optional<br>\r\n            </strong>Students are strongly encouraged to pay their tuition and other fees via inter-bank GIRO. Students who are keen to have their outstanding payment settled via GIRO are to input the Direct Debit Application (DDA) form, print, sign and submit it to the Office of Finance for processing.\r\n          </p></DIV>\r\n          \r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 7 - Register for Test / Camp / Talk</a></h3>\r\n          <div>\r\n            <p><strong>7.1 </strong><strong>Register for Waiver Tests<br>\r\n            </strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n              <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Waiver Tests <br>\r\n              <br>\r\n              </strong>Please click on the following links for information on the tests:<strong><br>\r\n              </strong>              &#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a> (Registration Deadline: 11 July) <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a> (Registration Deadline: 23 July)</p>\r\n            <p><strong>7.2 </strong><strong> Register for </strong><strong></strong><strong>Camps <br>\r\n            </strong><br>\r\n            <strong>7.2.1</strong> <strong>Register for SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp</strong> (4 runs)<br>\r\n            Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n            <strong>Navigation Path: </strong><strong>OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; </strong><strong>Camps \r\n            </strong> <br>\r\n              <br>\r\n              <strong>7.2.2</strong> <strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> to register for other camps:<br>\r\n              </strong>&#149;&nbsp; SSU Sports Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMUX Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SICS Freshmen Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMU Arts Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; School Camps </p>\r\n            <p><strong>7.3 </strong><strong>Register for Talks/Workshop<br>\r\n            </strong>Login to <strong></strong><a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>S</strong><strong>tudent Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n            <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS&gt; Home&gt; Pre-Term Activities and Info&gt; Talks <br>\r\n            <br>\r\n            </strong>Please click on the following links for information on the talks:<strong><br>\r\n            </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/Freshmen%202012_C4SR.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a> </p>\r\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 8 -              \r\n\r\n\r\n Fee Matters &amp; Financial Services</a> </h3>\r\n          <div><br>\r\n            Please click on the following links for information:\r\n            <ul>\r\n              <li><strong><a href=\"fee_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Fee Payment</a> </strong></li>\r\n              <li><strong><a href=\"financial_paymode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Payment Mode</a></strong> </li>\r\n              <li><strong><a href=\"financial_tga_SPR&IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tuition Grant Application</a> </strong></li>\r\n              <li><strong><a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/financial/assistance_schemes/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Student Financial Assistance Schemes</a></strong>            </li>\r\n              </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 9 - Other Important Information</a> </h3>\r\n            <div>\r\n              <p><br>\r\n    Please click on the following links for information:<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <strong><a href=\"downloads/Acad%20Calendar%202012-13.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Calendar</a> (PDF) <br>\r\n    </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_exemption.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Exemption Criteria </strong></a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_double.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Double Degree<br>\r\n    </strong></a><strong>&#149;&nbsp; </strong><a href=\"Leave%20of%20Absence.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong>Leave of Absence<br>\r\n    </strong></strong></a><strong><strong>&#149;&nbsp; </strong></strong><a href=\"Withdrawal.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><strong><strong>Withdrawal</strong><br>\r\n    </strong></strong></a><strong>&#149;&nbsp; </strong><a href=\"service_studentcard.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SMU Student Card</strong></a><br>\r\n    &#149;&nbsp; <strong><a href=\"service_ezlink.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Tertiary Student EZ-LINK Card</a><br>\r\n    </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/Locker%20Matters/locker.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Locker </strong></a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/students/student_life/services/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Insurance </strong></a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.smu.edu.sg/IITS/helpdesk_support/pc_spec/pc_tender.asp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>PC/Notebook Offer</strong></a></p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <h3><a href=\"medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Step 10 - Visit selected Raffles Medical Group clinic for Pre-Enrolment Medical Check-up</a> </h3>\r\n            <div>\r\n              <p>All students (both local and foreign) are required to undergo a <span class=\"red\"><strong>COMPULSORY</strong></span> medical examination with <strong>Raffles Medical Group (RMG) in Singapore</strong> prior to starting your studies at SMU. </p>\r\n              <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note: </strong></span>Kindly complete your medical check-up by <span class=\"red\"><strong>25 July 2012</strong>.</span> </p>\r\n              <p>Please <a href=\"medical_SG.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on pre-enrolment medical check-up.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 11 - Activities Prior IDs Verification Period </a> </h3>\r\n            <div>\r\n    Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk </strong></p>\r\n              <p><strong>List of Tests </strong><strong><br>\r\n                </strong><strong> </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"aca_english.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Writing Exemption Test</a> <br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_STAT.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for Statistics</a></p>\r\n              <p><strong>List of Camps<br>\r\n                </strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong><br>\r\n                </strong>&#149;&nbsp; SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Runs 1 - 3)<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SSU Sports Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMUX Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SICS Freshmen Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; School Camps (SOA, LKCSB1 and SOL) </p>\r\n              <p><strong>List of Talks/Workshop<br>\r\n              </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/Freshmen%202012_C4SR.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Community Service Briefing</a></p>\r\n            </div>        \r\n            <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 12 - <span class=\"red\">Part 2: IDs Verification </span></a></h3>\r\n            <div>\r\n            <div class=\"ctrtext\"><strong>Part 2: IDs VERIFICATION &amp; CARD COLLECTION VENUE<br> \r\n              </strong><br>\r\n                <strong>School of Accountancy <br>\r\n                Registration Point: Level 2, opposite the lift lobby</strong> <br>\r\n                Singapore Management University <br>\r\n              60 Stamford Road Singapore 178900 <br>\r\n              <br>\r\n              <div class=\"ctrtext\">\r\n                <table width=\"0%\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n                  <tr>\r\n                    <td bgcolor=\"#DFFFFF\" class=\"ctrtext\">Date &amp; Time <strong><br>\r\n                      <br>\r\n                      <strong><strong>30 July: 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong><br>\r\n                    </strong>                      (<span class=\"style2\">Note: </span>1st day session starts at 2.00pm) <br>                      \r\n                    <strong><strong><strong>31 July: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm <br>\r\n1 August: 9.00am - 11.30am / 2.00pm - 4.30pm</strong></strong><br>\r\n                      <br>\r\n                      </strong>                      (Note: Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012 , 5.00pm</u>) </td>\r\n                  </tr>\r\n                </table>\r\n                <p><br>\r\n                  Please <a href=\"verification_SPR.asp\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"bodytext red red\"><strong>click here</strong></a> for <strong><span class=\"red\">COMPULSORY</span> documents</strong> to be presented during the session.</p>\r\n                <p><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Matriculated students who do not turn up for the \'IDs Verification &amp; Card Collection\' exercise will have an administrative hold placed against them, which will result in them being barred from using certain e-services (such as register for courses).</p>\r\n              </div>\r\n</div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 13 - Activities During/After IDs Verification Period </a> </h3>\r\n            <div>\r\n              <p><strong>13.1 </strong>Attend <strong><a href=\"academic.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Academic Briefing</a> </strong>(This is crucial) </p>\r\n              <p><strong>13.2 </strong>Attend registered <strong>Test/Camp/Talk </strong><strong></strong></p>\r\n              <p><strong>List of Tests </strong><strong><br>\r\n              </strong><strong> </strong>&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"waiver_test_IS.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Optional Waiver Test for IS200/201/202</a></p>\r\n              <p><strong>List of Camps<br>\r\n                </strong>Please <a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/integrate.html\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on the camps:<strong><br>\r\n                </strong>&#149;&nbsp; SMU Freshmen Teambuilding Camp (Run 4)<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; SMU Arts Camp<br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; School Camps (LKCSB2, SOE, SIS and SOSS) </p>\r\n              <p><strong>List of Talks/Workshop<br>\r\n                </strong> &#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"downloads/OCS%20Orientation.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Career Services Orientation</a><br>\r\n&#149;&nbsp; <a href=\"Library.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Library Training Workshop</a></p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <h3><a href=\"#\">Step 14 - Register for Classes </a></h3>\r\n            <div> \r\n              <p>At SMU, all undergraduate students register or enroll for classes via a bidding system called BOSS (<strong>B</strong>idding <strong>O</strong>nline <strong>S</strong>y<strong>s</strong>tem). Each term, the students are given e$, which they use to bid for courses. This empowers them to draw up their own timetable based on personal choices and study plan, subject to the constraints of curriculum requirements, and the supply and demand of classes. </p>\r\n              <p>Please <a href=\"aca_boss.asp\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on course registration and BOSS. </p> \r\n            </div>\r\n              <h3><a href=\"http://freshmenexperience.smusa.sg/enjoy.html\" target=\"_blank\">Step 15 - Attend Convocation</a></h3>\r\n              <div id=\"accordion\">\r\n              <p>Convocation is a formal event with all the pomp and ceremony, and SMU\'s Chancellor, Chairman, President and faculty in full academic regalia on hand to welcome the new students to SMU. </p>\r\n              <p>Please <a href=\"www.smu.edu.sg/convocation\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for information on convocation. </p>\r\n            </div>\r\n  <h3><a href=\"#\">Start of Term</a> </h3>\r\n<div>  <p><strong>OASIS </strong></p>\r\n  <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note: </strong></span>Only students who have matriculated and activated SMU Computer Account can access <strong><em>OASIS</em></strong>! <br>\r\n      <br>\r\n      <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg/\">OASIS </a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg) stands for <strong>O</strong>n-Line <strong>A</strong>ccess to <strong>S</strong>tudent <strong>I</strong>nformation <strong>S</strong>ystem and hosts various self-service services under different categories such as Study, Personal &amp; Finances, Resources, Career &amp; Jobs, Student Life and Schools &amp; Community. <strong>Simply put, OASIS is your one-stop service centre</strong>. <br>\r\n      <br>\r\n  Please click <a href=\"downloads/OASIS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> (PDF) for an overview of the self-service services that are available through OASIS. </p>\r\n  <p>You are strongly advised to log in to OASIS regularly so that you do not miss out on the important announcements and services throughout your study life. <br>\r\n      <br>\r\n  If you need assistance in accessing or using OASIS, please contact: <br>\r\n  <strong><br>\r\n  IITS HelpDesk </strong><br>\r\n  Singapore Management University <br>\r\n  Basement 1, School of Accountancy <br>\r\n  Singapore 188065 <br>\r\n  Tel: +65 6828 0123 <br>\r\n  Email: <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\">helpdesk@smu.edu.sg </a><br>\r\n  <br>\r\n  <em><strong>Operating Hours </strong></em><br>\r\n  Mon - Fri: 8:30am -7:00pm (Last walk-in 6:30pm) </p>\r\n  <span class=\"red\"><strong>Reminder... </strong></span><br>\r\nAfter you have matriculated and activated your SMU Computer Account online, you will be given a SMU Email Account which you may access. Please check your SMU Email Account via <a href=\"http://live.smu.edu.sg\">http://live.smu.edu.sg </a> on a regular basis, in order not to miss out on important information from the University. </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n</div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearall\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"updated-info\" align=\"right\">\r\nLast updated on\r\n    <!-- #BeginDate format:Sw1 -->20 April, 2012<!-- #EndDate -->\r\nby <a href=\"mailto:registrar@smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"> Registrar\'s Office</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- <div id=\"gamma\"><div id=\"gamma-inner\"><div id=\"content-body\">\r\n<div align=\"center\"><br /> -->\r\n            \r\n	</div>\r\n	\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n','Singaporean PR','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-7','','','2012-04-26 11:48:23','2012-04-26 11:48:23','',86,'http://matt2012.super.21marinabay.com/86-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(217,1,'2012-04-30 07:32:19','2012-04-30 07:32:19','   [accordions title=\"Accordion Group Title\" active=1 event=\"click\" autoheight=true]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 1 - Make Payment (at least 2 days prior to Step 3)\"]\r\n<div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Make online payment <br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        </strong>        \r\n        <p>Make non-refundable Confirmation fee* of <strong>$203</strong> via credit card** or <a href=\"downloads/AXS%20Payment%20Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AXS Payment Stations </a>available island-wide. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"red\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: Allow 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system. Please make payment latest by<span class=\"red\"> 12 July 2012</span>. </p>\r\n        <div id=\"feeshighlight\">\r\n            <p align=\"justify\"><b>*One-Time Fee of S$203</b> <b><strong>(non-refundable) </strong></b>for Pre-Course Activities and Matriculation <font color=red>(NSMen are only required to pay in the year of admission)</font>. </p>\r\n            <p align=\"justify\" > \r\n      **The online credit card payment of confirmation fee can be made via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a>.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" >You may check the payment status via <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\">Applicant\'s Self Service</a> (Student Admission or Online Matriculation &gt; View Payment Status).\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    [/accordion]\r\n    [accordion title=\"Step 2 - Update/Verify of Personal Data\"]\r\n	         <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation&gt; Confirm Personal Data </strong><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p> Please take some time to confirm/update your personal data as captured in the official records. It is important for the University to maintain accurate data in case of emergencies. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n[/accordion]\r\n[accordion title=\"Step 3 Part 1: Matriculate Online\"]\r\n      <div>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a>  (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n        <strong>Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Matriculate Online</strong><br>\r\n        <br>        \r\n        <p>Please ensure that you have completed Step 1 and Step 2, at least 2 working days before you proceed with this step. Kindly ensure that all matriculation information is accurate.</p>\r\n        <p align=\"center\"><strong>Important Note</strong>: For students <span class=\"red\">below 18 years old</span>, please print out the indemnity form for submission during <strong>Part 2: IDs Verification Day</strong>.</p>\r\n        <table width=\"500px\"  border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"500\" bgcolor=\"#CCFFFF\" ><div class=\"ctrtext\"><strong>Part 1 - ONLINE MATRICULATION<br>\r\n                <br> \r\n                Date: 18 June 2012, 9.00am - 16 July 2012, 5.00pm</strong>\r\n                \r\n                <br>\r\n                <br>\r\n                (Note: Pay a non-refundable Confirmation Fee* by <span class=\"red\">12 July 2012</span>. Please wait for 2 working days for payment to be updated in the system.) <br>\r\n                </div></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n        <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n [/accordion]\r\n [accordion title=\"Step 4 - Activate SMU Computer Account\"]\r\n\r\n      <div>\r\n        <p>Login to <a href=\"https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Applicant\'s Self Service</strong></a> (https://eservices.smu.edu.sg/psp/ps/?cmd=login)<br>\r\n<strong> Navigation Path: Self Service&gt; Online Matriculation &gt; Activate SMU Computer Account</strong> </p>\r\n<p>Please remember your new SMU user ID &amp; Password. You will require your SMU computer account to access SMU\'s network resources such as\r\n\r\n\r\nthe student portal OASIS as well as the campus email.</p>\r\n        <p>Henceforth, you must use your SMU Email Account to correspond with SMU. Important email will be sent to that email account. Please check it regularly. </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      [/accordion]\r\n\r\n    \r\n       	\r\n	        [accordion title=\"Step 5 - Upload Photograph\"]\r\n	\r\n	      <div>\r\n	       <p>Login to <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Student Portal OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg)<br>\r\n          <strong>Navigation Path: OASIS> Home> Pre-Term Activities and Info> Upload Student Photograph</strong></p>\r\n        <p>Please use the newly activated account and login to the student portal  <a href=\"https://oasis.smu.edu.sg\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> OASIS</strong></a> (https://oasis.smu.edu.sg).\r\n      \r\n          <a href=\"http://info.smu.edu.sg/courses/Part_1_Matriculation/SMU_Guidelines_on_Taking_Photograph.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">          Approved photographs</a> will be used for printing onto the SMU Student Card, which will be issued to you during the IDs Verification Day. Applicants who have uploaded their photograph earlier will not need to re-submit, unless the photograph uploaded earlier does not meet SMU’s specification and is rejected. </p>\r\n        <p><span class=\"ctrtext\"><span class=\"style2\">Note:</span> Student\'s photograph must be submitted online by <u>16 July 2012, 5.00pm</u>.</span></p>\r\n \r\n	      </div>\r\n	      [/ac